

Repository always deal with entities
Controller layer will always deal with DTO's
primary keys of the entities should be matches with the DTO's it act as connector which will connect 2 classes.
We cannot use DTO's for repo/DB commit because it doesn't have table annotations.
We will not have all the columns in DTO only entity will.
DTO is used to masking the entity class that directly connected to DB for security

Mapper:
a) Request(DTO to entity):- source is DTO and target is entity  -> connector is primary keys
b) Response(ENtity to DTO):- source is entity and target is DTO


SwtichifEMpty is a similar to try/catch block whcih return one object(true) or throws exception(false)

step by step logic
1) user login(already created)
2) ticket booking using movie details+ user details
3) Payment based on this ticket should be booked/cancelled
